org.apache.flink.runtime.fs.s3

Class S3DataInputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • org.apache.flink.core.fs.FSDataInputStream
        • org.apache.flink.runtime.fs.s3.S3DataInputStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class S3DataInputStream
extends FSDataInputStream
    This class implements an FSDataInputStream that downloads its data from Amazon S3 in the background. Essentially, this class is just a wrapper to the Amazon AWS SDK.

      • seek

        public void seek(long desired)
          throws IOException
        Description copied from class: FSDataInputStream
        Seek to the given offset from the start of the file. The next read() will be from that location. Can't seek past the end of the file.
        Specified by:
        seek in class FSDataInputStream
        Parameters:
        desired - the desired offset
        Throws:
        IOException - thrown if an error occurred while seeking inside the input stream
